  "delivery-methods": {
    "handle": "delivery-methods",
    "title": "Delivery Information",
    "body": "<p><strong>How can I track my parcel?</strong><br>Once your order is packed and dispatched, we send a shipment confirmation email with your tracking link. Tracking can take a few days to wake up after dispatch, so do not panic if the page looks quiet at first. You can also check progress through <a href=\"https://www.thestreetlamp.com/apps/17TRACK\" title=\"Track your Order\">Track your Order</a> or inside My Account.</p>\n<p><strong>What delivery options do I have?</strong><br>Most orders arrive within 9-15 business days after shipping, not including customs processing. Busy periods can take longer. Orders ship from our Shenzhen warehouse in China, and customs delays are outside Street Collector control.</p>\n<p><strong>International shipping destinations</strong><br>We currently ship to Argentina, Austria, Brazil, Canada, Cyprus, Denmark, Finland, France, Germany, Greece, Hungary, Iceland, Ireland, Israel, Italy, Luxembourg, Norway, Poland, Spain, Sweden, Singapore, Switzerland, South Africa, Turkey, the United Kingdom, and the United States.</p>\n<p><strong>Shopping from a different country</strong><br>If you are browsing in one country and shipping to another, switch the market at the top of the site under International. Prices, delivery timing, and shipping charges can change with the destination.</p>\n<p><strong>Undeliverable parcels</strong><br>If a parcel cannot be delivered because of an incorrect address, unpaid customs fees, or a missed collection window, it will be returned to Street Collector. Reshipping fees may apply.</p>\n<p><strong>Import taxes and customs duties</strong><br>Prices on thestreetlamp.com do not include local VAT, sales tax, or import duties. If your order crosses your country&apos;s duty-free threshold, customs fees may be charged on delivery. Those fees are set by your local authority and are the customer&apos;s responsibility.</p>\n<p><strong>How do I pay customs fees?</strong><br>If duties apply, the parcel will be held at customs and your local carrier will contact you with the amount due and the payment steps needed before delivery can continue.</p>\n<p><strong>Bank fees</strong><br>Your bank may add cross-border transaction fees. Street Collector does not reimburse those charges, so check with your bank if you need exact details before ordering.</p>",
    "bodySummary": "Track your parcel by email or account, expect 9-15 business days after shipping, and note that customs, taxes, and bank fees may apply depending on your destination.",
    "updatedAt": "2023-02-01T10:35:40Z"
  },
  "contact-us": {
    "handle": "contact-us",
    "title": "Contact Us",
    "body": "<p>If you need help with an order, payment question, or anything else around Street Collector, reach out. We keep customer support in English and try to make the answer useful on the first pass.</p>\n<p><strong>Phone</strong><br><a href=\"tel:4684468399\">+972 050 5983 880</a></p>\n<p><strong>Email</strong><br><a href=\"mailto:Info@thestreetlamp.com\">Info@thestreetlamp.com</a></p>\n<p><strong>Support hours</strong><br>Weekdays, 9am-4pm (GMT+3)</p>\n<p><strong>Personal data requests</strong><br>Our support team can also help with personal data requests covered by the Privacy Notice. If you need to contact the Data Protection Officer, include <strong>DPO</strong> in the subject line.</p>",
    "bodySummary": "Contact Street Collector by phone or email for order help, payment questions, and personal data requests. Support is available weekdays, 9am-4pm GMT+3.",
    "updatedAt": "2022-09-05T14:30:33Z"
  },
  "seller-profile": {
    "handle": "seller-profile",
    "title": "Hen Macabi",
    "body": "<p>Chen Maccabi is a graphic designer, illustrator, and typographer. His practice centers on building visual and typographic languages for brands, whether they are already established or just getting started.</p>\n<p>The client work stretches across lifestyle, restaurants, fashion, cultural events, television, music, and entertainment. What carries through is the emphasis on identity: not just making something look good once, but giving it a voice that can hold up over time.</p>",
    "bodySummary": "Chen Maccabi is a graphic designer, illustrator, and typographer who builds visual identities for brands across lifestyle, fashion, food, music, and culture.",
    "updatedAt": "2022-11-20T16:28:42Z"
  },
