  "nia-stai": {
    "handle": "nia-stai",
    "title": "Nia.Shtai",
    "body": "<p>Levgeniia Batrushtai, known as Nia Shtai, was born in 1990 in Kharkiv, Ukraine. As a child she spent eight years in boarding school, during a period when repeated power outages turned ordinary evenings into improvised story hours. One of her teachers would have her stand on a chair and tell stories to the class. That mix of uncertainty and invention stayed with her.</p>\n<p>Years later, with war again reshaping daily life in Ukraine, art remains the place where she keeps hold of beauty without pretending the world is simple. Her paintings feel protective without becoming soft. She often speaks about them almost as living companions, a way of carrying experience outward instead of keeping it sealed inside.</p>",
    "bodySummary": "Nia Shtai, born in Kharkiv, carried childhood story rituals through blackouts into an adult painting practice shaped by memory, tenderness, and life under pressure.",
    "updatedAt": "2022-12-11T15:56:05Z"
  },
