    "title": "Tel Aviv Gifts and Home Decor by Working Artists",
    "excerpt": "",
    "contentHtml": "<p>If you want a gift that feels like Tel Aviv, skip the generic souvenir route. The city's art scene is full of work that carries its own texture, whether that comes through sharp typography, raw drawing, sculpture, photography, or objects that sit somewhere between design and art.</p>\n<p>Some pieces belong on a shelf. Some belong on a wall. The strongest ones do not try too hard to explain themselves. They bring a little of the city with them: the heat, the humor, the crowded visual language, the pull between polish and improvisation.</p>\n<p>That is what makes artist-made home decor worth hunting for. A print, a small edition, or a sculptural object can do more than fill a corner. It can set the tone of a room and carry a sense of place without feeling staged. Tel Aviv artists are especially good at that balance. The work often feels urban and lived-in, but still precise.</p>\n<p>When choosing a piece, look for something you would keep even if it were not labeled as a gift. That is usually the right test. The best finds from Tel Aviv do not land as souvenirs. They stay because they keep their charge once you bring them home.</p>",
    "imageUrl": "https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0659/7925/2963/articles/discover-the-best-tel-aviv-gifts-and-home-decor-from-modern-jewish-artists-261999.jpg?v=1731427492",
